In this article, President Joe Biden addresses the rising levels of antisemitism in the United States and around the world. He highlights the alarming increase in antisemitic incidents, including hate crimes, attacks on synagogues, and harassment of Jewish individuals. President Biden emphasizes the importance of remembering the atrocities of the Holocaust and educating future generations about its horrors. He also stresses the need to speak out against antisemitism and appoints a Holocaust expert as the first Ambassador-level Special Envoy to Monitor and Combat Anti-Semitism. Additionally, President Biden discusses the actions his administration has taken, such as signing a bipartisan law to combat hate crimes and increasing funding for the security of Jewish institutions. He announces the forthcoming release of a national strategy to counter antisemitism and calls on all Americans to actively confront bigotry. President Biden concludes by emphasizing the importance of preserving the values of religious freedom, equality, dignity, and respect, and uniting as one nation to reject hate and antisemitism.